---
description: Interpreting follow-ups and staying aligned with the user’s goal
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

## When

- The user sends a short follow-up after a longer thread.
- Requirements sound partial, or the latest message could be a refinement mid-task.

## Do

- Treat new messages in an active thread as steering the current work unless they clearly start a new topic.
- Infer the underlying goal (correctness, speed, UX, maintainability) and optimize for that.
- Ask one or two targeted questions only when blocking facts are missing.

## Don’t

- Ignore prior constraints or accepted decisions without explicit reversal.
- Reset context or re-derive everything from only the last sentence when history matters.
- Over-question when you can proceed safely with reasonable defaults.
